The paper is about information retrieval and natural language processing, which are both subfields of computer science. The use of named entities and ontologies in the proposed model suggests that it may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of latent information and machine learning techniques suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a dataset and the consideration of different ontological features suggests that it may also belong to the Database (cs.DB) sub-category.
